The paper discusses the design and implementation of a large-scale testbed for cloud computing, which involves distributed systems, networking, and software engineering. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the high-performance network services used in the testbed, which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the second most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses benchmarks, interoperability studies, and utilities for cloud computing systems and services, which are relevant to cs.Distributed Systems, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SE (Software Engineering), respectively.
